    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for adding `Bun.INI`:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe task requires touching **6 files** following the exact same 5-layer wiring pattern used by `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.JSONC`, `Bun.JSON5`, and `Bun.YAML`:\n\n### Files & Changes\n\n1. **CREATE `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — Self-contained INI parser + stringify (no dependency on internal `src/ini.zig`). Modeled after `YAMLObject.zig` with 2 functions:\n   - `parse`: Walks lines, skips comments (`;`/`#`), handles `[section]` headers (→ nested JS objects), and `key = value` pairs. Throws `SyntaxError` on invalid lines. All values are JS strings.\n   - `stringify`: Two-pass iteration — top-level scalars first as `key = value`, then nested objects as `[section]` headers. Uses `JSPropertyIterator` and `std.ArrayList(u8)`.\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n\n3. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — Add lazy prop constant, `@export` call in `exportAll()`, `getINIObject` getter function, and `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject` import\n\n4. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI)` between `Glob` and `JSON5` in `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n\n5. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI  BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI  DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `@begin bunObjectTable`\n\n6. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI` with `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string`, with JSDoc examples",
